{
  "stem": "14060.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 21.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And basically, what it consisted was that they bought up large tracks of agricultural land immediately in the vicinity of the town center or just the part which was going to develop.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They-- subsequently my father subdivided it, putting roads, built houses on it, some of it very industrial premises, which were let out like a timber yard and so on.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so much so that in the times of the 1940s, when Jews were basically being honed-- hounded in business and people didn't want to deal with them, we lived very comfortably.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Besides certain property investments, which brought a fixed income, also my father used to say that if we sell one plot of land, which we have many of them, we can live more comfortable than the amount of money we can spend.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So basically I had a-- maybe if you like to call it pampered, but a very comfortable, financially comfortable, background.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the family was one of the foremost families in town, due to the maybe education, maybe financial influence.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So I probably had more opportunity to meet people who were non-Jewish people who my father had dealings with, than let's say a simple shopkeeper who was serving textiles or fruits or whatever in the main thoroughfare.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The community, as such, was very interesting.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was quite separated, the Neolog and Orthodox communities, so much so that they had each their own butcher shop.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They were next door to each other.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They had all their own separate communal organizations.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They had separate cemeteries, even though they were next door to each other, which were separated by a wall.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And some cynics said that-- it was very heavily bombed, that town, in 1944, after our deportation-- that one wall, which was separated, the bomb hit it.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
